Talenza have been engaged by a QLD energy client to find a Business Architect
to work with stakeholders to effectively deliver on their technology product
portfolio. Ideally you will have experience in the energy sector or a similar
industry (mining or utilities).

  
An in-depth knowledge of business architecture and adept stakeholder skills
are essential to be successful in this role. Successful candidates must be
currently located in Brisbane with PR or citizenship.  
  
  
  
Benefits

  * 6 month day rate contract (likely extensions) 
  * Competitive day rate 
  * Highly flexible hybrid working (2 days per week in office) 
  * Tons of progression opportunities 
  * Amazing leadership group and office/team culture 

  
  
Responsibilities

  * Engage with business stakeholders to elicit product and business goals. 
  * Produce strategic product and business roadmaps inline with budgets and timelines. 
  * Explain technical concepts to technical and non technical stakeholders. 
  * Develop strong stakeholder relationships. 
  * Previous experience in the Energy Sector will be highly regarded. 

  
  
Thank you for your interest, at Talenza we are passionate about providing
equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity. We encourage people
with disabilities and those from diverse backgrounds to apply. However, please
note that we are only able to proceed with those who have full rights to work
in Australia. Please apply directly or for a quicker response, contact Lewis
Babcock (Talenza) through LinkedIn.

